      "locked": false,
      "fontFamily": 2,
      "fontSize": 15,
      "text": "Claude Opus: 3x more expensive, no noticeable quality gain on a structured task like this. Using Haiku here failed:\n~20% of reels came back garbled.\nSonnet wins: sweet spot. Reliable structure, rarely needs the auto-correcting fallback.",
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "middle",
      "baseline": 12,
      "originalText": "Claude Opus: 3x more expensive, no noticeable quality gain on a structured task like this. Using Haiku here failed:\n~20% of reels came back garbled.\nSonnet wins: sweet spot. Reliable structure, rarely needs the auto-correcting fallback.",
      "lineHeight": 1.25,
      "containerId": "el_TSyeVPQAzmqcat",
      "autoResize": false
    },
